<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment in Hainan's Public Transport Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Some 20 new airconditioned
public buses valued at 10 million yuan (1.25 million U.S.dollars)
started operation today in Haikou, capital of south China's Hainan
Province.
</P>
<P>
The buses are operated by the Haikou Hongyi Public Bus Co. Ltd., a
joint venture between the Haikou Public Transport Company
and the Macao Hongyi Co. Ltd., the largest public transportation
enterprise in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Haikou Hongyi was the first public transport company in the
city to use overseas investment after the island province of Hainan
became China's largest special economic zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
