<HEADLINE> Hailstorm Attacks East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, December 8 (Xinhua) -- A hurricane and hailstorm
attacked Zhangping City, Fujian Province in east China, on Sunday
morning, causing economic losses worth over one million yuan to
local people.
</P>
<P>
The natural calamities, which are rare in winter, caused
damages to houses of over 200 local families and over 20 ha. of
farmland.
</P>
<P>
Local governments have mobilized people to rescue the victims
soon after the appearance of the hailstorm and hurricane, while
local insurance companies have started to investigate the losses
and to pay the compensation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
