<HEADLINE> Zambian opposition parties register for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- More than 17 opposition parties
including the one led by former president Kenneth Kaunda have
registered for the inter-party dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Micheal Sata, national secretary of the ruling Movement for
Multi-party Democracy (MMD), today expressed happiness at the
response from the opposition parties.
</P>
<P>
He said here that the secretaries of political parties will
decide on the agenda of the planned dialogue when they meet on
Tuesday as no conditions have been set.
</P>
<P>
Sata hailed the opposition parties for registering without
setting any conditions.
</P>
<P>
This shows that they are serious about dialogue on various
issues that have remained unresolved between the MMD and the
opposition parties.
</P>
<P>
Among the parties which have registered are Kaunda's United
National Independence Party (UNIP), the Zambia Democratic
Congress, Liberal Progressive Front, the Unity Party for
Democrats, National Party, and National Lima Party.
</P>
<P>
The MMD set up an office here today to register for opposition
parties interested in the dialogue.
</P>
<P>
The inter-party talks failed to kick off as planned last July
after opposition parties renewed their calls for abolishing the
current constitution, establishing an interim government and
holding new elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
