<HEADLINE> S. Africa's ANC Denies Report About Winnie's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The African National
Congress (ANC) today denied that its Women's League (ANCWL) has
dropped Winnie Madikizela-Mandela from its nominations list for
the ANC's national conference in mid-December.
</P>
<P>
Madikizela-Mandela, ANCWL president and former wife of South
African President Nelson Mandela, is in bid for the ANC's
national deputy presidency at the conference in Mafikeng,
North-West province.
</P>
<P>
"Suggestions in the media that ANC spokespersons have
indicated that the ANC Women's League has decided to drop the
name of Winnie Madikizela-Mandela from their nominations list,
are wholly incorrect and devoid of all truth," the ANC said in a
short statement.
</P>
<P>
Madikizela-Mandela's reputation was marred to some extent
after she was implicated in 18 cases of human rights violations
at a nine-day Truth and Reconciliation Commission hearing.
</P>
<P>
Mandela is set to step down at the conference as ANC leader to
allow his deputy, Thabo Mbeki to step into his shoes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
