<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Deports 2,170 Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 8 (Xinhua) -- A total of 2,170 foreigners
were deported from Zimbabwe this year for contravening
immigration laws.
</P>
<P>
Most deportees were from neighboring Mozambique, who flout
immigration laws to come and work in Zimbabwe's commercial farms.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe's chief immigration officer Elasto Mugwadi said today
that most illegal immigrants ran away from economic hardships in
their countries to Zimbabwe which had also been identified as a
new base in crime.
</P>
<P>
The high rate of unemployment within other countries, he said,
was contributing a lot to the flouting of laws by foreigners who
normally engaged in unlawful employment and business once they
arrived in Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Other deportees were from Nigeria, Zambia, Malawi, South
Africa, Tanzania, Ghana and Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
