<HEADLINE> Two Leading Swiss Banks Merge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Two leading Swiss banks today
announced plans to merge and establish a new bank called the
United Bank of Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The two banks, the Swiss Union Bank and the Swiss Bank
Corporation, are two of the three biggest banks in Switzerland.
The new bank after their merger will be the second biggest in
the world only behind Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi.
</P>
<P>
The United Bank of Switzerland to be based in Zurich will have
a total of assets and liabilities worth 922 billion Swiss francs
(about 658 billion US dollars), according to local press reports.
</P>
<P>
The merger will result in loss of a total of 13,000 jobs in
three to four years. 7,000 employees to be out of work will be
Swiss citizens. 
</P>
