<HEADLINE> Swiss Banks Merger Threatens UK Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 8 (Xinhua) - Up to 2,000 highly paid City
workers could lose their jobs after Swiss Bank Corporation (SBC)
and Union Bank of Switzerland (UBS) announced today a full merger.
</P>
<P>
The merger will create the world's second largest commercial
bank, with assest of nearly 600 billion US dollars, after HSBC
Holding plc.
</P>
<P>
The combined bank aims to cuts costs at home, to match the top
German and Japanese banking groups in technology and to challenge
the market dominance of American global investment banks.
</P>
<P>
"The merger was aimed at remaining a leading global player in
five or ten years," UBS chief executive Mathis Cabiallavetta, was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
City experts said that the move follows a series of bank
mergers in Britain, Japan, the United States and even Germany.
</P>
<P>
SBC and UBS said they would shed some 13,000 jobs overall over
the next three to four years if their merger is approved by their
respective shareholders in February.
</P>
<P>
There are fears that London could be badly hit because of
duplication in the bank's operations. Over 2,000 people in the
City will lose their jobs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
