<HEADLINE> Liver Transplant for Five-day Girl in London </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Surgeons have replaced the liver
of a five-day-old girl, making her the youngest organ transplant
recipient in the world.
</P>
<P>
Details were emerged today of an operation given to baby
Baebhen Schuttke, from Ireland, at King's College Hospital in
London, last July.
</P>
<P>
Doctors at the hospital said they were able to give the baby
the gift of life through a pioneering technique which reduced a
donor liver to one-eighth of its normal size.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference in London, the girl's mother Ita
said, "We can't believe it. We are so delighted and overwhelmed by
the whole brilliant and miraculous outcome that has occurred."
</P>
<P>
Ita and her husband have lost their two sons to the same
conditions.
</P>
<P>
Ita said her baby "is no trouble to look after. She is just
like any other ordinary baby." 
