<HEADLINE> Nigeria Urged to Overhaul Teachers' Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 8 (Xinhua) -- A Nigerian educationist today
called for a total overhaul of teacher's education to improve the
training and supply of science and technology teachers in the
country.
</P>
<P>
A program for the training of emergency teachers in science
and technology could not be ruled out if Nigeria was to enter the
21st century with hope and confidence, said Prof. Dibu Ojerinde,
registrar of National Board for Educational Measurement in Minna,
Niger state.
</P>
<P>
Teachers' education in Nigeria has been defective since the
advent of western education, particularly the curriculum which is
devoid of science content, he said.
</P>
<P>
"This resulted in producing teachers who had little or no
knowledge of science. The teacher education curriculum showed
emphasis on arithmetic only and mathematics with all its
importance left out," the News Agency of Nigeria quoted the
professor as saying.
</P>
<P>
While calling on the government to professionalize teaching
and give teachers a special salary scale, Ojerinde pointed out
that the quality of science graduates must also improve.
</P>
<P>
"Several graduates can hardly communicate scientific knowledge
in meaningful ways to their pupils or hardly recognize scientific
apparatus and equipment, talk less of having ability to mount up
experiments or demonstrations in school laboratories," he said.
</P>
<P>
This had led to ill-prepared teachers teaching ill-prepared
pupils and under-achievement in science, he told a lecture
organized by the Science Teachers' Association of Nigeria.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
