<HEADLINE> U.S. Secretary of State in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine K. Albright arrived here tonight on a two-day working
visit to further ties with Ethiopia and discuss African issues.
</P>
<P>
The visiting U.S. secretary of state is expected to meet
senior government officials including Prime Minister Meles Zenawi
and Foreign Minister Seyoum Mesfin for talks to this end,
according to the Ethiopian Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Albright will also meet Salim Ahmed Salim, secretary general
of the Organization of African Unity (OAU), and K.Y. Amoako,
executive secretary of the United Nations Economic Commission for
Africa (ECA), mainly to discuss with them about African issues.
</P>
<P>
She is scheduled to make a speech entitled "The United States,
Africa and the Great Lakes" here on Tuesday morning to African
diplomats.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is the first leg of her seven-nation African tour
which also includes Uganda, Rwanda, the Democratic Republic of
Congo, Angola, Zimbabwe and South Africa. This means that the
U.S. attaches importance to the role of Ethiopia in Africa's
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Albright was sworn in as the secretary of state in January
this year. She is the first female secretary of state in the
history of U.S. government. 
