<HEADLINE> Education in Eritrea Develops in Last Four Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The total number of pupils
and students in Eritrea has increased to 349,514 from only
168,803 during independence in 1993, the Eritrean Ministry of
Education has announced.
</P>
<P>
According to the announcement, the present number of schools
in the country, including private and government schools, stands
at 729, compared with only 190 schools in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Among them, high schools have doubled from 16 to 37, while
elementary and junior schools jumped from 174 to 692.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the number of teachers in Eritrea has more
than doubled from 3,672 in 1993 to 7,764.
</P>
<P>
According to the Eritrean ministry, the government spent over
60 million Nakfa (about 8.3 million U.S. Dollars) in building
schools in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The expenditure has increased to 300 million Nakfa (about 41.6
million US Dollars) during the last three years from 1995 to
1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
