<HEADLINE> Turkey to Explain Its Military Cooperation With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Turkey will explain its
controversial military cooperation with Israel at the upcoming
summit of Organization of Islamic Countries (OIC), according to a
Foreign Ministry spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing here, Sermet Atacanli said
that Turkey will clarify its position on the Turkish-Israeli
military cooperation so as to clear up misunderstandings of the
Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
Iraq and Syria, two Arab neighbors of Turkey, have reportedly
prepared a motion for the OIC summit calling for a collective
condemnation of Ankara's closer military ties with the Jewish
state.
</P>
<P>
"The references in the resolution did not quite reflect the
truth of the issues," Atacanli said.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that Turkey's cooperation with Israel in defense
and military fields is not directed against any other country.
</P>
<P>
According to earlier reports, Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel will head an official delegation at the eighth OIC summit
scheduled to be held Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The rapidly increasing military contacts between Turkey and
Israel have aroused grave concerns among the Arab countries in
the Middle East, which accused Turkey of betraying the interests
of the Muslim world.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Israel signed two defense and military training
agreements last year to allow joint warplanes exercises in each
other's airspace. 
