<HEADLINE> Kuwait, Syria Sign Agreement of Avoiding Double </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and Syria signed an
agreement of avoiding double taxation here today at the end of a
two-day meeting of the joint committee between the two countries,
the Kuwaiti News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Deputy Prime Minister and Finance Minister Nasser
Abdullah Al-Rudhan and Syrian Deputy Prime Minister Saleem Yaseen
signed the agreement, according to the agency.
</P>
<P>
After the signing ceremony, Al-Rudhan said that subjects of
politics, economy, transportation, agriculture, culture and
tourism were discussed at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Yaseen said that agreement is reached by the two sides on
promoting bilateral trade and that a symposium will be held in
Syrian capital Damascus on upgrading mutual investment.
</P>
<P>
He arrived here Monday for the sixth meeting of the joint
committee since it was set up in early 1990s to expand bilateral
trade and economic cooperation. 
</P>
