<HEADLINE> UK, France, Germany Urge Integration of Airspace Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 9 (Xinhua) -- France, Britain and Germany
Tuesday called for reorganizing the airspace and defense
electronics industries of Europe and transforming the Airbus
Industrie into an integrated company.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made in a joint communique released by the the
French presidential palace. The communique was signed by the heads
of state or government of the three nations.
</P>
<P>
"We agree upon the urgent need for a reorganization of the
airspace and defense electronics industries. This process should
include in the airspace sector, the military as well as civil
activities, and lead to a European integration founded on a balanced
partnership," the communique said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the first step would be transforming Airbus into
an integrated company.
</P>
<P>
French President Jacques Chirac, Prime Minister Lionel Jospin,
British Prime Minister Tony Blair and German Chancellor Helmut Kohl
also welcomed the intention of Daimler Benz Aerospace, Aerospatiale
and British Aerospace to combine their activities.
</P>
<P>
They asked these three groups to present a specific timetable
for reorganization and integration before March 31, 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
