<HEADLINE> Conference Recognizes Outstanding Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Some 298 outstanding students
and representatives from 200 model classes all over China were
honored today at a conference held in Beijing, the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The State Education Commission and the Central Committee of the
Communist Youth League (CYL) sponsored the conference to honor the
outstanding performance of students and class collectives from
across the nation.
</P>
<P>
Today's conference also marked the 62nd Anniversary of the
December 9th Movement, a demonstration Beijing students under the
leadership of the Communist Party of China staged on December 9,
1935. The demonstrating students called for resistance against
Japanese aggression and national salvation.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Yuanqing, vice minister of the State Education Commission,
attended today's conference and called on students to study hard
and devote themselves to the motherland. 
</P>
