<HEADLINE> China Leads Seeds into Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Every thing was in progress
as expected in the group matches of the 11th Asian Women's Soccer
Championship as China led seeds and the best runner-up DPR Korea
into the semifinals on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion China, Japan, Chinese Taipei and DPR Korea
made the last four after the group competition which ended Tuesday
without any surprises.
</P>
<P>
The semifinals will see China take on Chinese Taipei and Japan
clash with DPR Korea on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side rounded off their group B matches with a 16-0
battering of the rock-bottom Philippines, which skyrocketed their
goal tally to 27 out of their three group victories.
</P>
<P>
Japan, seed and comfortable leader in Group A, put the issue
beyond doubt by strolling past Hong Kong, China 9-0 at Panyu
Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Earlier at Zhaoqing, Chinese Taipei also made the semifinals as
it whipped Khazakstan 6-0 to wrap up Group C with a perfect record.
</P>
<P>
DPR Korea, smashing up Uzbekistan 8-0 and locking on six points
with Group A second-placers India, a 10-0 winners over Guam,
advanced on better goal difference.
</P>
<P>
The top three teams of the tournament will qualify to FIFA's
third World Cup for women soccer, which is to be held in the
United States in two years' time. 
</P>
