<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Unemployment Up in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The number of Germans on the
jobless list increased to 4,321,600, or 11.3 percent of the
country's total labor force, in November.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, the Federal Labor Office in Nuremberg said on
Tuesday, October's unemployment rate was 11.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Bernhard Jagoda, chief of the labor office, said 2,941,900
people in western Germany, or 9.5 percent of the total labor force
there, lost their jobs in November, 19,400 more than that in
October.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the official said, 1,379,800 people were dismissed
from their jobs in eastern Germany, an increase of 11,900 to hit
an unemployment rate of 18.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Germany's economic growth, Jagoda said, was not fast enough to
stop the loss of jobs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
