<HEADLINE> Fieldwork on Key Scientific And Economic Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- China will carry out a series
of fieldwork projects concerning key scientific and economic
problems in order to promote scientific and economic development,
according to Lu Yongxiang, president of the Chinese Academy of
Sciences (CAS).
</P>
<P>
Fieldwork serves as the foundation of scientific research
concerning resources, the environment, biology and agriculture, as
well as an important means for promoting high technology
application.
</P>
<P>
Lu told participants in the second CAS meeting on fieldwork,
which opened today in Beijing, that China's fieldwork should focus
on solving the key scientific and technological issues, including
global and regional climate changes, macrobiological evolution,
natural disasters, sustainable resources and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that thorough research of key issues will enable
China to further develop branches of learning such as resources
science, environmental and disaster science, macrobiological
science and oceanology.
</P>
<P>
Lu added that China should develop fieldwork stations into
national, and in some cases even the world bases for scientific
and technological experiments and research.
</P>
<P>
He called on Chinese scientists and technicians to focus on
problems related to food, the environment and health.
</P>
<P>
"We should also try to find a way to relieve poverty and ensure
the nation's prosperity," said Lu.
</P>
<P>
China will face pressing issues related to a growing population
and environmental deterioration in the forthcoming
century. China's population is expected to reach some 1.6 billion
by the year 2030, and the nation will suffer from a critical
shortage of resources such as arable land, water, and fuel.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
