<HEADLINE> Macao First Pop Singer to Make Debut in China's Inland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Pop song lovers in China's
inland will be able to hear the voice of a Macao pop singer for
the first time in history next year.
</P>
<P>
Casimiro Pinto, a Macao pop singer, is to make a debut for
China's inland audiences when his first CD album is published next
May or June in cooperation with the China Records Company in
Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
With a Portuguese father and a mother from Guangzhou, Pinto,
who works as an interpreter at a government department, will sing
in Portuguese and Standard Chinese (Putonghua) a song about the
return of Macao to the motherland in the new album, according to
an agreement signed by Pinto and the Guangzhou-based studio on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The song will be specially written for him, expressing the
feeling of a Macao-born Portuguese about the transition and return
of Macao," said Wu Songjin, a pop song composer and producer who
represents the China Records Company.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a piece of MTV program featuring the song will be
shot for him in Macao and Guangzhou. The program will be broadcast
both in China's inland television stations and Macao TV station.
</P>
<P>
Rita Santos, president of Pinto's promotion committee, said
that she hopes the coming album will help inland listeners know
better about Macao's culture, its people and history.
</P>
<P>
"Listeners in China's inland will be able to listen to the
'voice of Macao'," she said. "We consider the new album will
express the full confidence of Macao residents in their future and
their life after the handover of power in 1999."  
</P>
</TEXT>
