<HEADLINE> Industrial and Commercial Bank of China Opens Seoul Branch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC) opened its Seoul Branch Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bank set up its representative office in Seoul in 1994 and
the office was upgraded to branch-level in November this year, in
a bid to meet the increasing demands of economic-trade cooperation
and investment between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The ICBC, established in 1984, is one of the largest
state-owned commercial banks in China and is also ranked the fifth
among the top banks in the world in terms of total assets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
