<HEADLINE> German Inflation up to 1.9 Percent in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Germany's annual rate of inflation
rose to 1.9 percent in November, compared with 1.8 percent in
October, the Federal Statistics Office said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It blamed higher energy costs and travel spending for the
increase in the annual inflation rate last month.
</P>
<P>
In western Germany, the annual inflation rate rose from 1.7
percent in October to 1.8 percent in November, while that in
eastern Germany declined to 2.3 percent from 2.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The office added that overall, the cost of living in November
remained the same as in October. 
