<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Power Supplier Opens Office in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 9 (Xinhua) -- China Light &AMP; Power Company
Limited (CLP), which supplies the bulk of Hong Kong's electricity,
today opened its representative office in southern China's
Guangdong province.
</P>
<P>
Located in Guangzhou, the capital city of Guangdong, the new
office is to help promote CLP's interest in the growing power
industry in the province and its long-term development in southern
China, sources from the company said.
</P>
<P>
Michael Kadoorie, CLP's chairman, said: "CLP has a
long-standing, strong business relationship with southern China."
As early as the beginning of this century, CLP was supplying
power in Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
In 1979 when China started to adopt the open policy, the power
company interconnected its transmission system with the Guangdong
grid. Ever since then, it has participated in such projects as
China's first nuclear power station and the Guangzhou pumped
storage power station.
</P>
<P>
"Looking ahead, we have full confidence in the continued growth
of southern China," he said, "the establishment of the Guangzhou
office demonstrates again our firm commitment and determination to
play a key role in the power business in the region."  
</P>
