<HEADLINE> Switzerland Hails Four-Party Talks on Korean Peninsular </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland, the host country of
the four-party talks to seek a lasting and stable peace on the
Korean Peninsula, hailed the event as the possible dawning of a
new process.
</P>
<P>
In his opening address here Tuesday at the two-day talks, Jakob
Kellenberger, state secretary of the Swiss Federal Department of
Foreign Affairs, said: "We hope that this process will result in
the progressive introduction of confidence-building measures on
the Korean peninsula."
</P>
<P>
On the reason Switzerland plays host to the talks, Kellenberger
said, "Switzerland is very pleased to host these talks not only
because of their intrinsic importance but also because they offer
Switzerland the opportunity to contribute to detente in this part
of the world, albeit in an indirect way."
</P>
<P>
He said that Switzerland regards a lasting peace settlement on
the Korean peninsula as one of the key factors for securing
stability throughout the world.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from China, the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea, South Korea and the United States attended the talks.
</P>
