<HEADLINE> Hotel Earnings Down in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Hotel earnings in Macao this year
dropped by 15 to 20 percent compared with that of last year, the
Va Kio newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted the Macao Census and Statistics Department as
saying that due to a sharp decline in tourist arrivals since July,
Macao's hotel room occupancy rate decreased to less than 60
percent between July and October, down 18.87 percent from the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, many hotel owners have planned to trim their working
forces in the coming year by 10 to 20 percent, especially in the
areas related to cleaning and catering services, the paper said.
</P>
