<HEADLINE> Electronics Center Taking Shape in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, December 9 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province is
building an electronics center in the Fuzhou Development Zone.
</P>
<P>
So far, 94 electronics firms have settled in a
1.2-square-kilometer area designated as the first phase of
development. The companies are expected to turn out a combined
industrial output of 4 billion yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
Most of the enterprises in the electronics zone were built with
funds from Taiwan and other parts of the world. More than 40
percent of the projects are in the information technology field and
86 percent are export-oriented.
</P>
