<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Newspapers Hail NPC Deputies Election (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Major Hong Kong newspapers
today responded warmly to the election of the 36 deputies of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) to the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC) of China.
</P>
<P>
Almost all the major newspapers gave extensive coverage to
Monday's election of the HKSAR deputies. They devoted special
pages to the reports and photos about the election.
</P>
<P>
Many carried pictures and brief notes of the newly elected
deputies.
</P>
<P>
A commentary of the Ta Kung Po said that the 36 deputies
elected Monday, representing the Hong Kong people, will have the
right to join China's supreme organ of state power in the
management of state affairs.
</P>
<P>
This right is particularly prominent and precious for the Hong
Kong people who have just returned to the motherland after more
than a century-long colonialist rule and elected their own
deputies to the NPC as an independent constituency, it said.
</P>
<P>
The election, which was smooth, satisfactory and successful,
served as a lively education in patriotism to all the people of
the SAR.
</P>
<P>
Through this election, the Hong Kong people came to see that
they had become a part of the country after Hong Kong's return to
the motherland and have the same rights as the Chinese people in
other parts of China to participate in the management of state
affairs.
</P>
<P>
The commentary expressed the hope that the 36 deputies will
practice their duties, link up the connection between Hong Kong
and the inland areas and report to the Central Government the
SAR's actual situation and the real ideas of the Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that the people of the SAR will show their
support to the deputies and help them really play their role and
make their contributions as representatives of the SAR under the
policy of "one country, two systems".
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971209.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Newspapers Hail NPC Deputies Election (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Hong Kong Commercial Daily in its commentary said that the
election of the 36 HKSAR NPC deputies, the first group of deputies
elected by the Hong Kong people after Hong Kong's return to the
motherland, is a demonstration of the further implementation of
the policy of "one country, two systems" and the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The newly elected deputies are broadly representative because
they have been always loving the country and Hong Kong and have
made their contributions to the country and Hong Kong, it said.
</P>
<P>
Through this election, it said, the Hong Kong people have a
deepening understanding of the people's congress system of the
country, the role and position of the NPC in the political life of
the country, and the policy of "one country, two systems", as
well as of how the Hong Kong people can participate in the
management of state affairs.
</P>
<P>
A signed article in Wen Wei Po said that the 36 HKSAR deputies
to the NPC can represent the Hong Kong people because they are
from various sectors including industrial and commercial circles
and sectors of profession, labor, grassroots and religion.
</P>
<P>
When the Ninth NPC opens in Beijing next spring, it said, these
deputies will, together with representatives from other parts of
China, represent the interests and ideas of the Chinese people
including the Hong Kong people to discuss state affairs and put
forward their ideas about the prosperity of Hong Kong and the
rejuvenation of the Chinese Nation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
