<HEADLINE> East Chinese City Starts Files on Springs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The 293 famous historical springs
scattered throughout the famous "Spring City" of Jinan, capital of
east China's Shandong Province, now have their own files.
</P>
<P>
The files contain information covering each spring's location,
size, spillage, water temperature, related poems and photos.
</P>
<P>
Li Shixin, director of the Famous Spring Management Office,
said that the establishment of spring files will provide a
scientific basis for the future management and protection of local
springs, and serve the development of local tourism.
</P>
<P>
At present, the office is editing a set of books on famous
springs with contents covering legendary stories, poems, photos
and steles.
</P>
<P>
The office also plans to put related information on the
Internet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
