<HEADLINE> Sydney Experiencing Construction Boom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Sydney's construction boom was
generating projects worth 10 billion Australian dollars (6.7
billion US dollars), Premier Bob Carr of Australia's New South
Wales state said tonight.
</P>
<P>
The premier said the new figures released today showed that 3.8
billion US dollars of construction was underway and a further 3.1
billion US dollars was planned for Sydney, capital of the state.
</P>
<P>
"Sydney and New South Wales are experiencing a construction
boom due to international focus on the state - and these figures
do not include private sector investment outside the CBD (central
business district)," he said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
He said that "the Olympics (Games to be hosted by Sydney) alone
have generated 7,865 jobs on site and 15,730 jobs offsite."
</P>
<P>
"Hotel construction accounts for more than 1.3 billion
Australian dollars (870 million US dollars)," he said.
</P>
<P>
With a population of 4 million, accounting for 22 percent of
the country's total of 18 million people, Sydney has been the
country's leading business, financial and cultural center as well
as tourist attraction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
