<HEADLINE> China Coasts into Semifinals with Easy Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion China
entered the semifinals of the 11th Asian Women's Soccer
Championship after a 16-0 win over the Philippines in a Group B
match on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The victory left the home side with a maximum and unassailable
nine points out of three group matches with DPR Korea second on
six points after its 8-0 rout of Uzbekistan Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Earlier at Zhaoqing, Chinese Taipei also made the last four as
it whipped Khazakstan 6-0 to wrap up group C with perfect record.
</P>
<P>
The three group winners and the best runners-up advance into
Friday's semifinals.
</P>
<P>
China, five-straight-time champion, completely terrorised its
weak opponents, who did not even manage a shot on goal throughout
the match.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine defense cracked up on five minutes and the
Chinese girls closed out the first half at 5-0.
</P>
<P>
The scoreline soared into 11-0 in space of ten minutes in the
second half so that the Philippine coach decided to try out the
substitute goalie, only to come on dumbed by another Chinese
strike.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines, 21-0 victims by China at 10th championship two
years ago, lost all their group matches and saw their net tore
open for 32 times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
