<HEADLINE> Belgian General to Be New Chief of Eurocorps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Belgian Lieutenant-General Leo
Van den Bosch will take over as from December 15 the post of the
commander of the Eurocorps, Agence France-Presse reported today.
</P>
<P>
Van den Bosch will succeed French General Pierre Porterre.
</P>
<P>
The chief of staff of the French armed forces, General
Jean-Philippe Douin, will preside the ceremony of passing the
commander's seat from Porterre to Van den Bosch, in the presence
of Belgian Defense Minister Jean-Pol Poncelet and army chiefs of
staff of Germany, Spain and Luxembourg, the report said.
</P>
