<HEADLINE> S. African Vigilantes' Organization Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Secretary of South
Africa's People Against Gangsterism and Drugs (PAGAD), Abida
Roberts, was arrested early this morning in her Cape Town home
after being found in procession of a secret document, South
African Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
PAGAD is a paramilitary vigilantes' organization dealing with
crime and drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman said officers seized a secret document in
Roberts home which was allegedly leaked from parliament.
</P>
<P>
It was alleged that the document, originating from
intelligence sources, was marked for the attention of South
African President Nelson Mandela.
</P>
<P>
Roberts is expected to appear in the Cape Town Magistrate's
Court later today.
</P>
<P>
PAGAD accused the police of acting illegally when they
arrested Roberts, saying the police warrant only made provision
for the premises to be searched for weapons and ammunition and
that police were not entitled to search for documents.
</P>
<P>
Police denied PAGAD's claim and said the document seized was
within the ambit of the warrant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
