<HEADLINE> University Students in Tianjin Study Deng Xiaoping Theory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 9 (Xinhua) -- In today's China, young Chinese
find it is more and more difficult to totally agree with a
theory. However, Deng Xiaoping Theory seems to strike a chord with
young people.
</P>
<P>
This is particularly true for the 70,000 university students in
Tianjin, who have shown a great interest in the theory.
</P>
<P>
The university students here have established "Deng Xiaoping
Theory Study Society of University Students in Tianjin".
</P>
<P>
Ten of the municipality's 20 universities have set up
school-level academic forums on Deng Xiaoping Theory, which draw
tens of thousands of students. They have organized more than 500
study groups.
</P>
<P>
Nan Jingwei, an undergraduate from Nankai University, said:
"Deng Xiaoping Theory has brought earth-shaking changes to China
and is rich in content. We university students are deeply
interested in the theory."
</P>
<P>
Wu Hongjun, an official from the Tianjin Municipal Education
Committee, said: "Many courses on Deng Xiaoping Theory are
available in the universities, and they are warmly welcomed by the
students."
</P>
<P>
"We have decided to set up municipal-level symposiums first for
university students to study Deng Xiaoping Theory in the next few
months."  
</P>
</TEXT>
