<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yunnan Stages Trade and Investment Fair in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The southwestern Chinese
province Yunnan staged a trade and investment fair here today,
eyeing closer links with Hong Kong, its No. 1 investor and trading
partner.
</P>
<P>
The fair was the second of its kind with the first one held in
early 1993, Secretary-General of the Yunnan Provincial Government
Yang Chongyong told the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
For the five years from 1993 to 1997, trade between Yunnan and
Hong Kong is estimated to total over 1.8 billion U.S. dollars,
with an average annual growth of over 20 percent, the official
said.
</P>
<P>
As of November 1997, Hong Kong has invested 670 projects in
Yunnan, or 43 percent of the total foreign-invested projects, with
the contracted investment reaching 780 million U.S. dollars, 43
percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has become Yunnan's largest economic and trading
partner, Yang noted, expressing the hope that bilateral
cooperation would be further broadened.
</P>
<P>
The fair, running through to Saturday, brought some 400
projects for potential Hong Kong partners. A great number of the
projects involved the province's four pillar industries: tobacco,
biological resources development, mineral resources development
and tourism.  
</P>
</TEXT>
