<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Toyota to Build New Assembly Plant in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese automaker Toyota
announced today that it will build a new assembly plant in Onnaing
near Valenciennes in the Nord sub-prefecture of France.
</P>
<P>
Hiroshi Okuda, the president of Toyota, announced the decision
here after having a meeting with French Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin.
</P>
<P>
This will be the second plant to be constructed by Toyota in
Europe. Toyota has already have a plant in Burnaston in the
Midlands of Britain.
</P>
<P>
The new plant, which will enter service in 2001, will have a
production capacity of 150,000 vehicles a year. It will construct
a model specially designed for the European market, said Toyota in
a communique.
</P>
<P>
Toyota will invest 80 billion yens (about 615 million
U.S. dollars) in the plant, which will create 2,000 jobs in a
direct way, said Okuda.
</P>
<P>
He said that the establishment of Toyota in France is "an
important step" for the group in enhancing its "European
engagement."
</P>
<P>
Jospin said that the choice of Onnaing by Toyota as the site of
its new plant means that "the competitiveness of France is
appreciated abroad."
</P>
<P>
While hailing "the more and more marked interests" by Japanese
investors in France, Jospin said that the Toyota plant will bring
about "new technologies and new methods of industrial management,
as well as the possibilities of multiple industrial cooperation."
</P>
<P>
The mayor of Onnaing Daniel Crepin said that his city will
celebrate the decision of Toyota with a festival this evening on
the streets and in cafes.
</P>
<P>
"This will be a spontaneous festival. We have nothing to
predict until the official announcement," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971209.0166 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Offers Arms Package to S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Russia has bid to sell
150 Mig-29 fighters, 150 T-80U main battle tanks and four 636
diesel submarines to South Africa, local daily, the Citizen
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The arms package also include six maritime research and rescue
helicopters and six anti-submarine helicopters, a visiting
Russian delegation was quoted as saying at a press conference in
Pretoria Monday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation said the proposal would include offset programs
in South Africa of up to 80 percent of the contract value.
</P>
<P>
The offset programs would include establishing factories for
the assembly of the Aviatika-890 ultralight multi-purpose
aircraft and a light business aircraft in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Russia would consider establishing a heavy truck
manufacturing plant here and would become involved in mining
technology, education and other ventures.
</P>
<P>
The tender follows invitations by South Africa to the
international armaments industry to come up with proposals to
fulfill its armed forces' armament needs as outlined in the
Defense Review earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Pretoria has made it clear in putting out the tender that it
would require agreements which would include delayed payment for
the armaments acquired as well as substantial offset of the
contract amount through job and wealth creation programs here.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the Mig-29 to be sold to South Africa is
an upgrade of the older model with a range of 3,500 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The T80U battle tanks is a 46 ton tank with a 125 mm
smoothbore gun capable of firing both projectiles and laser
guided missiles. It is also equipped with active armor which uses
explosives to stop incoming projectiles and missiles.
</P>
<P>
It has a maximum speed of 70 km/h and can travel at speeds of
up to 35 km/h on rough terrains. Russians claimed that the tank's
engine was not very particular about fuel, namely it can run on
diesel, petrol or paraffin or any combination of the three fuels.
</P>
<P>
The 636 diesel submarine is an advanced attack submarine with
a range of up to 7,500 miles at a steady seven knots. It has a
maximum speed of 19 knots submerged and 11 knots on the surface.
</P>
<P>
The submarine has a stealth design and is armed with 653 mm
torpedo tubes. More than 90 of these submarines have been
exported to 154 countries throughout the world.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Russia, Britain, Germany and Spain have also
been trying to sell packages of weapons to South African armed
forces which complains that some key arms in use are either
obsolete or in poor condition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971209.0167 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Big Gas Field Discovered in China's Tianshan Mountains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Hutubi region at the
northern foot of northwest China's Tianshan Mountains has been
verified as a large natural gas field containing geological
reserves estimated at 30 billion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
The gas field, inside Hutubi county of the Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region, is about 60 kilometers from Urumqi, the
regional capital, south of the Tianshan Mountains and north of the
Junggar Basin.
</P>
<P>
In August of 1996 one testing well promised a daily output of
780,000 cubic meters of natural gas and 140,000 tons of light oil.
</P>
<P>
The Xinjiang Petroleum Administration sank two new testing
wells this year. They also followed that by using advanced
three-dimensional seismic technology for further exploration. The
two test wells produced high-yield gas flows in November, and now
have a daily output of more than 500,000 cubic meters
</P>
<P>
Workers also tested for gas on the well sunk in 1996 and have
increased the daily output to 940,000 cubic meters of gas at one
depth and 1.17 million cubic meters at another depth.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Professor Ou Yuande, vice
president of the Xinjiang Petroleum Research Academy, said that
Hutubi county has 120 square kilometers of oil-bearing land, with
a verified geological gas reserve of 31.3 billion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
Oil experts say that six similar major gas-bearing geological
structures also exist in the 12,000-square-kilometer area at the
northern foot of the Tianshan Mountains and the southern edge of
Junggar Basin.
</P>
<P>
The discovery and verification of the large gas field in Hutubi
county offers high hopes for other sites.
</P>
<P>
China also has found thick gas-bearing strata in a number of
testing wells sunk in nearby areas, indicating that the northern
side of the Tianshan Mountains could become an important
production center of natural gas in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
Exploration, development and a comprehensive use of natural gas
resources in Junggar Basin have been accelerated. By the end of
this century, Junggar Basin expects to have 200 billion cubic
meters of verified natural gas reserves and produce three billion
cubic meters of gas a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
