<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Medical Conference Honors Doctor for Cancer Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Li Zhe, a doctor of
traditional Chinese medicine who is famous for curing cancer with
Chinese remedies, has been honored by the 1997 Hong Kong
International Academic Exchange Conference on Medical Science and
Medicine.
</P>
<P>
Li, head of the Changchun Institute of Anti-Cancer Medical
Materials, developed Zhu Xiang Powder, a special medicine in
powder form made out of 17 kinds of Chinese medicinal herbs which
has been effective in treating cancer of the liver, lung, brain
and kidney.
</P>
<P>
Li, born in a family of doctors of traditional Chinese
medicines, suffered from breast cancer 20 years ago. The
experience encouraged her to seek a cure.
</P>
<P>
The effective rate of Zhu Xiang Powder in a strict two-year test
performed by the Institute for the Control of Drugs and Biological
Products proved to be 72.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Li submitted a paper, "Clinic Observation for 856 Treatments of
Carcinoma with a series Traditional Chinese Medicine -- Zhu Xiang
Powder," to the Hong Kong conference, which aroused great interest
among medical experts.
</P>
<P>
So far, Li has won 16 awards both in China and abroad. The
Oriental Medicine Institute in the United States has granted her
titles of "honorary chairman" and "guest professor."
</P>
<P>
The conference was designed to promote exchanges between
Chinese and Western medicines and to show the achievements of
today's medical science.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen other doctors were also honored at the conference.
</P>
</TEXT>
