<HEADLINE> Asian Lifter Dominate Women's 59-kg Competition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, Northern Thailand, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Asian
weightlifters dominated the women's events by sweeping a string of
medals in the 59-kilogram category at the World Championships here
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian girl Patmawati captured two gold medals in the 59-kg
class, lifting 97.5 kilograms in the snatch event, and 212.5 kgs
overall.
</P>
<P>
Suta Khassaraporn brought the hosts their first-ever world
championships title, clinching the gold of clean-and-jerk with
117.5 kgs, some 7.5 kgs below her own world record set last
October at the Southeast Asian Games in Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
In the women's categories of 46, 50, 54 and 59 kgs, Asian
competitors grabbed 12 golds, nine silvers, and 12 bronzes.
</P>
<P>
The only new world record so far in the women's competition was
set by China's Meng Xianjuan, who lifted 117.5 kgs in the
clean-and-jerk contest of the 54-kg category on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
