<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forcing Schoolgirls to Marry Illegal: Tanzanian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian Prime Minister
Frederick Sumaye has ordered school children to report to
relevant authorities if their parents force them to get married.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister made the directive last weekend when
addressing public rallies at Msangano and Iyula villages in the
Mbozi District during a tour to the Mbeya Region in the
southwest, according to The Guardian today.
</P>
<P>
He said stern measures would be taken against parents who
forced their school children, especially girls, to get married.
</P>
<P>
Any girl who learns that her parents want her to marry should
report immediately to divisional secretaries, the premier
directed, after knowing that school attendance in most primary
schools in Mbozi District was declining because of early
marriages.
</P>
<P>
Forcing schoolgirls to get married is a criminal offense and a
violation of their rights to education, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
He said anybody found guilty of making a schoolgirl pregnant
would be severely punished. 
</P>
</TEXT>
