letter Monday to the PNA, warning them that any census in
Jerusalem would violate the autonomy accord.
</P>
<P>
Kahalani also ordered the Israeli police to take whatever
steps necessary to stop such activities in the city.
</P>
<P>
During its preparations for this census, the PNA said it will
stay out of East Jerusalem to avoid a confrontation with Israel.
</P>
<P>
According to the census plan, the census will last until
December 24, and the final results are expected to be announced
on January 4, 1998. 
