<HEADLINE> Australian Official Foresees Steady Trade Growth With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Trade and exchanges of visit
between China and Australia are going to grow rapidly in the next
few years, Australian Minister for Foreign Affairs Alexander
Downer said here today.
</P>
<P>
Downer, arriving here at noon, wasted no time to emphasize the
Australian Government's commitment to expanding its relations with
China.
</P>
<P>
In a short speech at the inauguration of the new annex of the
Australian Embassy in Beijing at 1:30 local time, Downer said that
Australia is ready to further expand the "strong, rapidly growing
ties with China."
</P>
<P>
He noted that trade between the two countries will continue to
grow at a rapid rate as in the past ten years. He said that the
number of Chinese people visiting Australia every year will
increase from 56,000 in 1996 to 139,000 in 2001.
</P>
<P>
There are two important features of the strong, rapidly growing
relations between Australia and China. One is trade, the other is
people-to-people exchanges, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that physical expansion of the Australian Embassy is
parallel to the development of good bilateral relations because
the consul and trade sections of the Embassy are located in the
new annex.
</P>
<P>
Downer will stay in Beijing till Thursday morning before going
to Xi'an in northwest China.  
