<HEADLINE> Northwestern Region Nears Record High in Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The total export value of
northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region in the first 10
months of this year reached 209 million U.S. dollars, up 43.6
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The region is expected to record a historic high in exports
this year.
</P>
<P>
An official in the regional bureau of foreign economy and trade
attributed the growth to efforts made by state-owned companies
specializing in foreign trade, production-oriented enterprises
with the right of import and export, and foreign-funded businesses
in the region.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that between January and October, state foreign
trade companies earned 123 million U.S. dollars in exchange, a
13.8 percent increase over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Local products such as coal, cashmere, tires and tantalum (a
metallic element that resists corrosion) sold better than last
year in the international market. The export value of coal, for
example, reached 16 million U.S. dollars, 110 percent more than
the same period last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
