<HEADLINE> China's Gold Output to Hit 150 Tons This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- China's gold output is expected
to reach 150 tons this year, or 30 tons more than the previous
year, according to Wang Dexue, director of the Gold Administration
under the Ministry of Metallurgical Industry.
</P>
<P>
According to Wang, gold production between January and November
topped 137.1 tons, up 28 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
China's gold sector has fulfilled the targets set for 2000,
three years ahead of schedule. "Hopefully, China will become one
of the world's five major gold producers," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China's gold enterprises this year have identified
372 tons of gold reserves to be extracted.  
</P>
