<HEADLINE> Government Pays Attention to Investor Complaints </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has received 1,282 complaints from overseas investors in
two years ending in June, Vice Provincial Governor Gao Guozhu said
here recently.
</P>
<P>
So far, 1,165 -- 92 percent -- of the complaints have been
given satisfactory answers, Gao said.
</P>
<P>
Of the total complaints, 887, or 60 percent, concerned foreign
investors' disputes over the production and investment environment.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has approved 15,000 foreign-funded
enterprises with a total contractual value of 24.7 billion
U.S. dollars. Some 7,000 firms have become operational.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to deal with disputes between Chinese and overseas
partners in a timely manner, the province has set up complaint
centers in 14 cities and opened government hot lines. 
