<HEADLINE> Eighth Islamic Summit Opens in Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The eighth summit of the
Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC) opened here today
with the participation of 54 of its members.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest ever get-together of the 55-member Islamic
body since it was established 27 years ago. The seat of
Afghanistan is left vacant because the OIC was divided as to who
should represent the country. Afghan President Burhanuddin
Rabbani is attending the meeting as an observer.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 presidents, vice-presidents, emirs and crown
princes are present at the summit, together with thousands of
officials and representatives.
</P>
<P>
The three-day summit commits itself to promoting "dignity,
dialog and participation" in the Islamic world and is expected to
address a wide range of issues faced by the Muslims.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the summit, the OIC foreign ministers held a two-day
meeting on December 6-7 to debate and give endorsement to more
than 140 draft resolutions. The drafts will be further discussed
at the summit for final approval. 
</P>
</TEXT>
