<HEADLINE> Clouds of Industrial Recession Loom Large in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The clouds of industrial
recession seems to be looming large in India with some industries
recording a massive negative growth in September this year, the
local press said today.
</P>
<P>
According to an official news release issued on Monday, the
industries which registered two-digit negative growth included
wood and wood products (- 18.9 percent), electrical machinery and
parts (- 16.9 percent), and transport equipment and parts (-
10.5).
</P>
<P>
Over all industrial production growth in September this year
has been pegged at 2.4 percent vis-a-vis the 8.4 percent
achievement in the same month of last year.
</P>
<P>
The average industrial production in the first six months of
the current fiscal year (from April 1997 to March 1998) has been
set at 4.7 percent, which is less than half of 10.7 percent
achieved in the same period of last year.  
</P>
