<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman Says Clinton's Meeting with Wei Jingsheng Is Wrong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- China today expressed its
"strong resentment against and firm opposition to U.S. President
Bill Clinton's recent meeting with Wei Jingsheng".
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang said here
this morning when responding to Chinese reporters.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that reports say U.S. President Clinton recently met
with Wei, who was released on parole for medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
"This act of the U.S. side is totally wrong, and the Chinese
side expresses its strong resentment against and firm opposition
to the meeting," the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
