<HEADLINE> China Sweeps Six Titles at World Weightlifting Champs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, Northern Thailand, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Meng
Xianjuan set a world record to lead China for a sweep of all the
six titles on Monday at the world weightlifting championships.
</P>
<P>
Meng Xianjuan wrapped up the three golds in the women's 54-kg
category, and set a world record of 117.5 kilograms in the clean
and jerk, eclipsing the listed make of 115.5 gks set by compatriot
Liu Xiuhua last July.
</P>
<P>
Chinese strong man Wang Guohua snatched 175.0 kgs in his third
attempt to win the 64-kg snatch title, which was the 400th gold
medal presented at the world weightlifting championships.
</P>
<P>
Wang was awarded a special trophy by the International
Weightlifting Federation (IWF) to honor the milestone title in the
tournament's history.
</P>
<P>
Former World champion and the current Turkish national coach
Naim Suleymanoglu presented the memorable trophy to Wang on behalf
of the IWF.
</P>
<P>
Wang's teammate Xiao Jiangang took the clean and jerk as well
as total gold with 175.0 kgs and 317.5 kgs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
