<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Baltic Fleet to Enhance Regional Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Baltic Fleet should
endeavor to enhance its military cooperation with the countries in
the region, Commander Vladimir Yegorov said in Kaliningrad Monday.
</P>
<P>
Yegorov said the fleet's current military cooperation with the
Baltic States does not conform to the "needs of the age."
</P>
<P>
The Russian Telefax News Agency quoted Yegorov as saying that
Russia has not signed a pact with the Baltic States on the
prevention of accidents on the high seas or in airspace as it has
with the United States, Japan, Britain and France.
</P>
<P>
In addition, building a unified international search and rescue
system is also an urgent task facing the nations in the region.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the Baltic fleet's contacts with foreign countries,
Yegorov said the fleet has visited only 24 countries since 1990,
while it has received delegations from 66 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
