<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive Leaves for Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of
China, left here this morning for his first duty visit to Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure, Tung told reporters at the airport that
he would make a full report to President Jiang Zemin and Premier
Li Peng about all that has happened in Hong Kong since July 1.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Beijing, Tung will hold a full range of
meetings and discussions with other officials including Liao Hui,
director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office, on economic,
financial, livelihood issues as well as on future development of
the SAR, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
Asked for his comment on the work of the SAR government in the
months after he took office on July 1, Tung said that everything
is normal and very good.
</P>
<P>
Tung is scheduled to return Thursday.  
</P>
