<HEADLINE> Uzekistan, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan to Enhance Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Uzbekistan, Kazakhstan and
Kyrgyzstan signed several documents on improving cooperation
Monday in the Uzbek capital of Tashkent, the press here reported.
</P>
<P>
The documents call for the three central Asian countries to
expand cooperation in tourism and agriculture. They will also join
hands in coordinating the operation of the Central Asian Bank and
creating a regional stock market.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the three countries have decided to establish a
committee to monitor the cross-country narcotics trade, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The documents were signed at a regular meeting of government
leaders from the three countries.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the countries' premiers discussed the
issues of establishing a united economic system and realizing
economic integration.
</P>
<P>
The three premiers also agreed to set up a banking consortium
for each department to give full play to some 50 agreements signed
previously.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to meet in March to discuss the plans for the
banking consortiums. 
</P>
</TEXT>
