<HEADLINE> Research and Adjust, says CPC Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, made the
remarks here Monday during his meeting with Do Muoi,
general-secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of Vietnam (CPV).
</P>
<P>
"This is the fundamental way to keep the vitality of the
socialism," Li stressed.
</P>
<P>
While briefing on the recently-closed 15th National Congress of
the CPC, Li said socialism had its development process. There were
various stages, and each stage had its own special features.
</P>
<P>
"The basic task to ensure the healthy advancement of socialism
is to realize and make research on the various stages and
formulate policies and principles according to their features," Li
said.
</P>
<P>
He said socialist countries should participate in international
cooperation, learn from other countries' experiences and absorb
all the beneficial civilization fruits of mankind.
</P>
<P>
"This is an important condition for socialist countries (in
order) to keep constant development with the trend in the world,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
Li arrived here on December 7 for a four-day official good-will
visit to Vietnam. 
</P>
