<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader On Productivity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Historical experience has shown
that the way to consolidate and advance socialism is through
productivity, said a Chinese leader here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, made the
remarks during his meeting with Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van
Khai.
</P>
<P>
The essence of socialism is to emancipate and develop
productivity and eliminate exploitation so as to reach a common
good, he said.
</P>
<P>
Only by encouraging productivity and improving people's live
can society become stable, power be consolidated and the beautiful
dream realized, he added.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that Vietnam has experienced many important events in
its reform and opening drive, and China would like to share those
experiences with the Vietnamese in order to advance the cause of
modernizing socialism.
</P>
<P>
Khai agreed with Li. He said that learning from each other and
strengthening contacts between the two sides is significant if the
two countries are to follow the socialist path.
</P>
<P>
Li is on a four-day official good-will visit to Vietnam.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
