<HEADLINE> Brazil's Coffee Exports Up in Ten Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Brazil exported more
than 12.26 million sacks of coffee (60 kilograms each) in the
first ten months of this year, 2.69 million sacks more than that
in the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Press reports here said today that the coffee exports earned
2.31 billion U.S. dollars for the country, 90 percent up from last
year.
</P>
<P>
Germany and the United States are the two main buyers with each
having imported some 2.03 million and two million sacks. 
</P>
