<HEADLINE> Former Boxing Champ Gomez Arrested for Cocaine Possession </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 9 (Xinhua) -- Former three-time boxing
champion Wilfredo Gomez was arrested and charged with alleged
cocaine possession in the town of Loiza in Ruerto Rico.
</P>
<P>
Gomez was found using cocaine on Monday in his car along a
stretch of public beach and police officers confiscated six small
bags of the drug.
</P>
<P>
Gomez, 41, was taken to the Judicial Center in Carolina, a San
Juan suburb, and charged. He was freed on 1,000 U.S. Dollars
bond. His lawyer, Fernando Iglesias, denied the charges.
</P>
<P>
Gomez held the titles of World Boxing Council super
bantamweight and featherweight as well as the world junior
lightweight crown in the 1980s. He lost most of his assets soon
after retiring and had previously been arrested for investigation
of domestic violence and cocaine possession. 
</P>
</TEXT>
