<DOCNO> XIE19971209.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Plunges Lowest Against US Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 9 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian rupiah fell
deeper Monday, breaking the 4,100 barrier to touch another
historic low, while the stock market managed to make a three-day
rally, dealers and brokers said today.
</P>
<P>
Currency dealers said spot rupiah fell to a historic low of
4,155 against the U.S. dollar Monday afternoon, compared with last
Friday's close of 4,025.
</P>
<P>
The drop occurred despite sporadic intervention by Bank
Indonesia, the central bank, to support the currency.
</P>
<P>
Bank dealers said the rupiah was weighed down by concerns over
President Soeharto's health, fire at the central bank building and
some regional weaknesses.
</P>
<P>
Worries over Soeharto's health surfaced last Friday when the
76-year-old leader failed to attend a government function and a
senior minister announced the he was taking a 10-day rest to
recuperate from a recent overseas trip.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah's dramatic drop coincided with a fire Monday at Bank
Indonesia's headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The fire engulfed the top four floors of the bank's new
25-story A tower, killing 15 people.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah has lost 40 percent of its value since July amid
steep drops in currencies across Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Despite the weakening rupiah, stock prices on the Jakarta Stock
Exchange continued to rally. The composite index gained 2.1
percent to close up 8.835 points at 423.613.
</P>
<P>
Stockbrokers said the rise was due more to support from
state-owned enterprises rather than fundamentals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
