<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Light Industry Production Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 9 (Xinhua) -- China has witnessed a steady
increase in its light industrial production and export volume
during the first 10 months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The total output value of light industry in the January-October
period jumped by 14.1 percent to 1,957.5 billion yuan (235.8 US
dollars) by official count.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate registered 0.9 percentage points higher than
the national industrial output value and 1.7 percentage points
higher than the heavy industry output value.
</P>
<P>
Today's "China Daily" reports that 64 percent of the 25 major
light industry products maintained a stable increase in production
over the same period last year while the remaining 36 percent went
down.
</P>
<P>
The products enjoying stable growth include air-conditioners,
washing machines, milk products, soft drinks, beer and
freezers. Major decreases in production occurred in the newsprint
industry, electric fans and bicycles.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, exports of light industry products increased
greatly. According to Customs figures, from January to October
1997, total exports of light industrial products went up 22
percent to 43.25 billion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
