<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FIFA Unveils Four-man Roster for Player of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERNE, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's Ronaldo, soccer's 1996
player of the year, was named by FIFA in Zurich on Monday among a
four-man shortlist of candidates for this year's award.
</P>
<P>
Joining the Inter Milan forward at the award ceremonies at
Disneyland Paris on January 12 will be another Brazilian, Real
Madrid defender Roberto Carlos, and Arsenal's striker Dennis
Bergkamp of the Netherlands, and Juventus's French midfielder
Zinedine Zidane.
</P>
<P>
The shortlist was voted by 128 national team coaches around the
world. Only three players were shortlisted in previous years, this
year, however, the number extended to four as two players
receiving the same amount of votes.
</P>
<P>
Other awards to be handed out include the Fair Play award to
the fans of the Irish Republic, one to United States player Julie
Foudy for her efforts to the fight against child labour in the
football industry and to Josef Zovinec, an amateur player from
Slovakia, who played 60 years without a booking.
</P>
<P>
The evening will be highlighted by the induction of Pele, Franz
Beckenbauer, Michel Platini and Bobby Charlton as the first
players in the International Football Hall of Champions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
