<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Barbados Foreign Minister Visits Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Minister of Barbados
Billie Miller started today a visit to Cuba in advance to the 25th
anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between
both nations.
</P>
<P>
Miller, who was also deputy Prime Minister and Minister of
Tourism and International Transportation, will stay in Cuba until
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
She is expected to sign a cooperation accord Tuesday with Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Miller's agenda during the visit includes official talks with
her Cuban counterpart, Roberto Robaina, and Minister of Foreign
Investment and Economic Cooperation Ibrahim Ferradaz.
</P>
<P>
Miller's trip followed last week's visit by Barbados Prime
Minister Owen Arthur who attended the 8th Conference
Europe-Caribbean and the 4th Meeting of the Commission
Cuba-Caricom (the Caribbean Community).
</P>
<P>
These visits coincided with the 25th anniversary of the
establishment of diplomatic relations between Cuba and Barbados in
December 8, 1972. 
</P>
</TEXT>
