<HEADLINE> Technology Stocks Rise Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial
average retreated but technology stocks rose Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 38.29 points to 8,110.84.
Otherwise, it would continue its march toward its all-time best
close at 8,259.31, set August 6.
</P>
<P>
Stocks were pressured by another weak day in the bond market,
where interest rates rose for the third straight session.
</P>
<P>
As bond prices fell, the yield on the 30-year Treasury rose to
6.13 percent, up from late Friday's 6.09 percent. The yield fell
as low as 6.01 percent on Wednesday, its lowest finish since
January 1996.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a 6-to-5 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 489.63 million shares as
against 556.95 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 list, which on Friday closed at a
record high for the first time since early October, fell 1.42 to
982.37. The NYSE composite index, which also set a new high on
Friday after a two-month drought, fell 0.87 to 513.44.
</P>
<P>
But the technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 17.64 to
1,651.54; the Russell 2000 index of small companies rose 3.97 to
442.03; and the small-company dominated American Stock Exchange
composite index rose 3.22 to 673.49.  
</P>
</TEXT>
