<HEADLINE> Jordanian Crown Prince Meets US Military Officer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan met
with Commander-in-Chief of the U.S. Central Command Anthony Zinni
here today.
</P>
<P>
He discussed with Zinni issues of military and economic
cooperation between the two countries, especially U.S. military
assistance to meet the needs of the Jordanian armed forces, the
official news agency Petra said.
</P>
<P>
Zinni arrived here Sunday for a five-day visit ahead of the
delivery of 16 U.S.-made F-16 jet fighters, which are worth 200
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The fighters are expected in Jordan on December 17.
</P>
<P>
The United States decided to grant Jordan 300 million U.S.
dollars worth of military aid in 1994 after the kingdom signed a
peace treaty with Israel.
</P>
<P>
A year ago, Jordan received 100 million dollars worth of
military equipment as part of the aid package, which included 18
helicopters, 50 tanks, 250 trucks, two personnel boats, air-sea
rescue boats, machine guns and 1,000 night-vision goggles.
</P>
<P>
Jordan ranks the fifth top recipient of U.S. aid. 
</P>
